comments: Smallest m such that m^3 begins with n^2.
links: Moshe Levin, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: a(4)=55 because 55^3=166375 begins with 4^2=16. - _Moshe Levin_, Oct 18 2011
mathematica: s={}; Do[If[n==3, AppendTo[s,21], k=1; While[(ra=Range[Ceiling[(n^2*10^k)^(1/3)], Floor[((n^2+1)*10^k)^(1/3)]]) == {}, k++]; AppendTo[s, ra[[1]]]], {n,100}]; s (* _Moshe Levin_, Oct 18 2011 *)
